Ordered delivery, food arrived nice and warm, and quickly.  Portion sizes were great for the cost, and the quality was great.  I always tend to over-order on my first order at a new place (in case of small portions), and so I ordered a Western burger, loaded classic fries, and onion rings.  The burger was 100% fine, not the best I've had, but perfectly acceptable. The quality of the ingredients was good, just a tad bit on the dry side for my taste (seemed like a lean burger). I think next time I'll try a different burger rather than the Western, but it's probably just personal preference.  The onion rings were some of the best beer battered onion rings I've ever had, the batter was superb, and they weren't way too sweet like some battered onion rings I've had. They also held up remarkably well for delivery.  However, the main reason I'm giving this 5 stars is the loaded classic fries.  Loaded fries are one of my favorite foods on this planet (especially with chili), and AJ's made the best I've ever had. There was plenty of chili and cheese without making the fries soggy, and I never had a dry fry. The quality of the chili was great, and the perfect consistency. The jalapenos on top gave a great amount of spice, but may be a bit much for some people. Overall super balanced, and a perfect portion size for the cost. From now on I'll definitely just grab a burger and a loaded fry.

First, I'm from Chicago,  so if you're looking for a Chicago Style Italian Beef, while this restaurant does "technically" serve just that, it is the equivalent of Taco Bell being Mexican. The beef seems to be pre-sliced/refrigerated for what tastes to be a good amount of time. I say this because you can taste their refrigerator on the beef. Also, the beef is both very dry and sometimes cold. This is because they don't keep the beef on the warmer to cook properly like a traditional Chicago Style joint. Keep in mind this happened on several occasions while dining in and out. I only say this due to the employees having explained the wrapping and transport of takeout "makes the beef dry?". Next, the sweet peppers have on more than one occasion tasted as if they're past their prime. Further, their AJ's loaded fries are topped with the following: canned jalapenos,  canned nacho cheese,  canned chili and some type of nasty ranch dressing.  If you are eating in, expect a foul smell at their location. Keep in mind, some of their soft drinks are stale as well. Finally,  the icing on the cake...Last time I was in there, one of the employees picked his nose just before packing my order. Sure it was just off to the left, but I am an alert person who pays attention to details. Throw that in with their employees acting as if none of them want to be there and pretty much look through you when you try to talk with them, you will be sure to have a wonderful experience.  The only reason I've given them 2 stars is because it's the only Chicago Style restaurant around here. You're better off driving 70 miles to Merrillville in order to get Portillo's Italian Beef.

I have eaten at AJ's a lot of times and would have to say it is usually disappointing. I would have to say the main reason I have ordered multiple times over the last five years is the times they actually make a good bacon burger. I have had an instance where in my loaded waffle fry was a gnat.... could have been a fly but looked more like a gnat. I called about it and the manager did not really seem like he cared asked if I wanted another one I said no because it kinda grossed me out and it was late. The insect was smashed on the side of one of the waffle fries. A lot of the times the burgers come soggy when delivered this has happen on numerous occasions. The soggy burger issue seems to be getting better has not happen in awhile. What has finally made me write this review is the fact that I tried to place an order for delivery before 2:45 am, which is the time on hungry boiler that says they stop delivering and they told me they are not delivering. I asked what if I had placed an order thru hungry boiler and they said that they will cancel it. It does not matter if it is a minute before the time you stop delivering if you get an order you should make and deliver it. Overall this place is pretty over priced but if you get lucky you might get a decent burger delivered.
Great tasting Chicago style food without even having to leave your house. I recommend a CBR (Chicken Bacon Ranch) and a loaded waffle fry.
This used to be one of my favorite places. I would grab a sub from jimmy johns and fries from here. However, their cleanliness has really gone downhill. I won't be back

After seeing their tv commercials I couldn't wait to eat there. So went for lunch with a co-worker today...we both were totally disappointed!!  The person ringing us up must have been new...didn't know much about the food. I'm ok with that and understand.  The food was for the most part gross. Frozen and fried. A step above a very bad drive-in.  They say that their burgers are never frozen...unfortunately I had the breaded loin and a fountain drink. $8 and change. Not worth it at all. My coworker had a sandwich mozzarella sticks and a drink $15 and change. She was very disappointed in price and quality. She will never eat there again.  This was the Lafayette location by Wal-Mart. Maybe the other locations I hear of are better. One can only hope.  Don't bother trying...it simply isn't worth it.

The worse Italian beef EVER!! Of course the people of Lafayette may think its good but im from chicago. So i go and get a cup of nacho cheese thinking it will mask the taste i had to pay 1.06 for a CUP OF CHEESE which i was upset abt because the sign said 60¢. Never will i eat here again they have better Italian beef in gas stations in chicago then they do at aj. I only rated them to write this review otherwise No 🙅 Stars!!! If you have NO TASTE BUDS then ajs italian beef is perfect for you. Im so disappointed im 4 months pregnant and have been craving a beef. Never again!!!

As a former chicago resident, it's nice to get a taste of home while living in Indiana. Their chicago style dogs are textbook, right down to the celery salt. Their fries are just right and their burgers are great too. Once had a question about ingredients and the manager ripped the box apart from the back and let me read the ingredients panel for myself. Location is nice and convenient from Purdue's campus, I eat there about 1 a week on average.  Only downside is ventilation is a bit lacking, so it can get smokey during busier times, but they are aware of the problem and try to clear out the air if it ever becomes a problem.  AJ's is the Portillos of Indiana. If these guys ever leave, I will shed many tears.

Went here with a couple co-workers for lunch one afternoon and had a good homemade burger and waffle fries. A little on the expensive side, but worth it. Definitely worth a try if you don't want those fast food burgers.
